generif.text: regulated expression of EEG-1 is involved in the orchestrated regulation of growth that occurs as erythroblasts shift from a highly proliferative state toward their terminal phase of differentiation.
Caprin-2 promotes activation of the canonical Wnt signaling pathway by regulating LRP5/6 phosphorylation.
Caprin-2 C1q-related domain forms a flexible homotrimer mediated by calcium, and this trimeric assembly is required for the functioning of caprin-2.
findings revealed an unrecognized role of Caprin-2 in facilitating LRP5/6 constitutive phosphorylation at G2/M through forming a quaternary complex with CDK14, Cyclin Y, and LRP5/6.

name: caprin family member 2
summary: The protein encoded by this gene may regulate the transport of mRNA. It may play a role in the differentiation of erythroblasts. Multiple transcript variants encoding different isoforms have been found for this gene. [provided by RefSeq, Feb 2016].
